The need for speed The Run is fighting all over America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed by a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it into a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills to some extent everyone's ambition but it's useless if no one wants to do something else.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aging Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from the playable parts that would not only count with points.
So we were curious what the added passages will be in which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite well distinguished from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty, even if the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in heavily snow-covered mountains is very visually pleasing.
The events are more often than not adorned with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly diminishes your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition, the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you race against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then again another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police that enters the game and tries to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
Rather, it is an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
As a result, it is good because this element is not likely to interfere and, in the context described above, is placed in the elements that adorn the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go somewhere else.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the difference of the driving model, that of collisions is not yet at the point.
We do not expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy turns.
Or find yourself in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The reboot is done so that when you broke your face or went out in the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
It is therefore more a tool, in case something is not happening properly, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes reboots do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering the piece of itinerary in question.
The main drawback of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain corners that you have to go through in a certain way otherwise it does not go through.
Otherwise you will encounter "civil" vehicles in the same configuration at a given location as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds ahead or one minute late.
What annoys are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and circumvent them or brake them.
It does not matter if you go to meet him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent ahead of you in the same place.
This annoys you the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of the other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a lot of times.
It can be understood that the purpose of this game is to make something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's a pity because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You need to pay attention to gas pumps on the routes as you can change cars there however most of the time you have enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American engines for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic twists on highly technical lines, for example on laced roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog feature, which compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the hardest strokes to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
At the editorial we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about the creation of this game or if the authors really take us for idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What is embarrassing is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer of use to you.
The sound is good and the track is a choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack has been created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game feels like it's not finished.
The fun is really good but get ready for mistakes to hit your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
Students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the Rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of the Charles University are performed.
The objective of Festa Academica is not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Chore Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all information on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a tough war.”
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role," Miléna Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law, the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the various organs of the EU and their relations in such a understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from the Faculty of Law at Charles University might envy her, she showed how she takes her motto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Mrs Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
"From the very beginning there was criticism that he is dull, that he is a round-of-leather, that he can't fulfill any mission and I have to say that he has taken everyone's breath away because he holds his role to perfection."
“He is a man who can listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe.”
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the unity and greater readability of the Union's policy towards states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to forbid us our syrecky (baked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech presidency a success two years ago.
The Czechs either resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized an Eastern Partnership Summit.
It called the fall of the government a very negative one and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved today.
In addition, the new seven-year budget of the Union must be approved, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it would appear that the budget will be slim and cost-saving, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For a understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels nobody makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or that nobody has forbidden us to make syrecky.
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe is waiting for us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, she said, stems from several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this group from Visegrad still doing?' and he is not happy at all."
According to Ms Vicenova, in the near future, new tough fiscal rules are waiting for the member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed, Europe that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the zone.”
“We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute of Enhanced Cooperation.”
In the first place, it was said that the countries that want it and those that do not want it are cooperating between them remain in their corners.
"There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a really two-speed Europe," said Vicenova.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all themes with an impact on the EU should be discussed among all EU members and not just the members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the term that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest would be "the long term".
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s chief executive, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved as long as people are eager to think.
His slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson’s carefully crafted company culture.
For us IBM means long-term thinking of continuous forward-looking movements.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has allowed us to transform technology, business and society during our first century.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more "delayed for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, took care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic – IBM people were the only among the first American employees to have paid vacation, insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-crafted system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
Society was at first brilliant at discovering talent—as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and so could have a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has done so-called jamy, online brainstorming from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
An institution with a good name
