On the day the Supreme Court met behind closed doors to discuss the issue of political discord, whether opposition to President Obama's health law will be heard, two of its judges, Antonin Scalia and Clarence Thomas, were noticed at a dinner sponsored by the law firm that will defend the case in the high court.
