Austria (disambiguation)
Insertion of a "Golden Rule" in the Constitution
The ruling Social-Democratic/Christian-Democratic government in Austria on Tuesday decided to include in the constitution a "golden rule" budget in order to reduce public deficits and thus avoid a possible degradation by the rating agencies of the sovereign rating of Austria (triple A).
It was the Social Democratic Chancellor Werner Faymann himself who announced this decision after a council of ministers, while the Austrian public debt is 74.6%, well above the maximum 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty, but well below the debts of countries such as Italy, Greece or Spain.
“If Austria’s solvency were lowered by a single notch, from AAA to AA+, we would have to pay an additional three billion euros in interest every year,” said Deputy Chancellor and Christian Democratic Foreign Minister Michael Spindelegger.
Austria is thus following a request from the eurozone member countries at the Brussels summit on 26 October: the heads of state and government had then called for the inclusion by the end of 2012 of the reduction of public deficits and a return to the balance of the public accounts in the constitution or in a law of the same value.
The scheme adopted by the Austrian government is closer to the "German model", as Germany was the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017, the structural public deficit will have to decrease by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, as of 2017, the federal government’s structural public deficit will not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional states as well as municipalities will have to present balanced budgets.
The objective is to raise public debt by 2020/21 under the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty.
